        rdfs:label             "Albert Salomon (musician)" ;
        mtp:hasAbstract        "Albert Salomon (Hebrew: אלברט סלומון; July 21, 1935 – November 20, 2020), also known as \"Albert the Bulgarian\" (Hebrew: אלברט הבולגרי), was a Bulgarian-Israeli accordion player and social activist. He was also known for aiding the homeless in Tel Aviv for which he was recognized as a beloved resident of the city. Salomon used to throw street parties on a regular basis at his former upholstery shop in Tel Aviv and would invite the homeless under his care to come and attend." ;
